PROGRAM.NAME: Child Health Plus
PROGRAM.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: CHIP helps families provide health insurance to their children. It makes health care affordable for children of eligible families and covers all the medical care growing children need to avoid getting sick, plus the medical care that will help them get better if they do get sick or get hurt.
PROGRAM.INFO_HTML: CHIP program is managed by State Agency for Child Health Insurance Program. You can veiw the list of CHIP plans available to you or enroll in the program by visiting www.chipmedicaid.org

PROGRAM.NAME: Individual and Families Plans
PROGRAM.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: You can get coverage from different insurance companies in your state based on your and your family's health care needs. Premiums and cost will depend on the plan, platinum plans offering the highest premiums and lowest out-of-pocket costs.

PROGRAM.NAME: Medicaid
PROGRAM.SHORT_DESCRIPTION: Medicaid offers medical and health coverage to people with limited income. Medicaid is a state run program funded by both state and federal government. The groups covered by Medicaid are Pregnant women, children and people with disabilities.
PROGRAM.INFO_HTML: Medicaid program is managed by State Agency for Medicaid. You can veiw the list of Medicaid plans available to you or enroll in the program by visiting www.medicaid.gov

You get federal subsidy on exchange plan if your household has a moderate income level.
